  <datafield tag="545" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Universal Hagar's Spiritual Church was founded by George W. Hurley in 1923 in order to promote the study of the science, phenomena and philosophy of spiritual religion and is based in Detroit. The church is also affiliated with Hagar's School of Mediumship and Psychology and the Knights of the All Seeing Eye.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection includes material from the early years of the church's operation, but the majority of the collection documents church activities after the year 2000. included are publications, records of annual convenings, organizational miscellanea, scattered correspondence, and program materials.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="506" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
